This paper discusses the integration of various technologies in networking, including in-building networks, micro zones, and intelligent micro cells, which are all related to network infrastructure and communication systems (cs.NI). The paper also mentions adaptive frequency allocation and intelligent antenna systems, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). The integration of audio, video, data services, multimedia, and broadcasting suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM). The use of an intelligent approach for optimizing network performance and reducing power consumption is related to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the ill effects of cellular growth, which could be related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) as it may involve privacy and security concerns.
